Key Match Events: Australia won the ICC Men's ODI Cricket World Cup title for the sixth time after beating in-form India by six wickets.
Travis Head made 137 in just 120 balls.
Post-Match Reflections: Heartbreak for Rohit Sharma's team and millions of fans who were hopeful that the team will life the World Cup for the third time in their history.
Miscellaneous Highlights: India was not the favourite for the trophy in the final.
Bhullar wins Indonesia Masters and takes home the trophy.
The win took Bhullar to fourth place on the Asian Tour Order of Merit.
Others: The Australian cricket team once again lived up to their serial winners tag.
